<header class="header">
  <h1>Best Soil Blocker for Seed Starting</h1>
  <p class="tagline">
    The tool matters — but the system matters more.
  </p>
  <p class="lede">
    <strong>For most gardeners, the best soil blocker is one that produces consistent blocks quickly and works well with a properly prepared soil mix.</strong>
  </p>
  <p>
    Soil blockers are one of the most efficient ways to start seeds without plastic containers. They create dense soil cubes that hold their shape and encourage strong root development.
  </p>
  <p>
    But success depends less on the blocker itself and more on how consistently it performs in your workflow.
  </p>
</header>

<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>Quick Answer: What Should You Look For?</h2>

  <div class="quickAnswerBox">
    <ul class="plainList">
      <li><strong>Best overall:</strong> sturdy blocker with consistent compression.</li>
      <li><strong>Best feature:</strong> uniform block size.</li>
